ed purchasing power I-Bonds via TreasuryDirect\tGovernment-backed inflation hedge; rate adjusts with CPI\t$25\t4.03% composite rate\tTreasuryDirect.gov\tCreate account, link bank, buy $25-$10,000/year\tGuaranteed to beat inflation by fixed rate (currently 0.90%); $1,000 = ~$40/year tax-deferred Reduce Variable-Rate Debt\tProtects against rate spikes if dollar weakness causes higher rates\t$0\tSaves 15-28% APR\tCall card companies, refinance options\tPay minimum + any extra on highest-rate card first\t$1,000 paid down @ 24% APR = $240/year saved in interest Tier 2: INTERMEDIATE PROTECTION ($50-$500 Entry) Strategy\tWhat It Does\tMinimum to Start\tCurrent Rate/Return\tWhere to Do It\tExpected Input\tExpected Output CD Ladder\tLock in current rates before further cuts\t$100-$500\t3.5%-4.5% APY\tAlly, Marcus, Discover\tSplit funds across 3, 6, 12-month CDs\tPredictable returns; liquidity every 3 months as CDs mature Fractional Gold/Silver\tHard asset hedge against dollar decline\t$1 minimum\tGold up 20% YTD; Silver up 60% YTD\tVaulted, OneGold, JM Bullion, or fractional shares via Robinhood (GLD, SLV)\tBuy $25-$100/month in fractional gold/silver ETFs or physical\tPortfolio diversification; historically moves inverse to dollar International Stock ETF (Small Position)\tExposure to non-dollar denominated assets\t$1 (fractional)\tMSCI ACWI ex-USA: +29% in 2025\tFidelity, Schwab, Robinhood\tBuy VXUS, VEA, or IXUS ($25-$100 position)\tGain when dollar weakens vs other currencies Tier 3: ADVANCED STRATEGIES (For Those With $500+) Strategy\tWhat It Does\tMinimum to Start\tCurrent Rate/Return\tWhere to Do It\tExpected Input\tExpected Output TIPS (Treasury Inflation-Protected Securities)\tPrincipal adjusts with CPI\t$100 (via ETF)\tReal yield: 1.35%-1.89%\tTreasuryDirect or TIPS ETFs (SCHP, TIP)\tBuy TIPS ETF through brokerage\tInflation-adjusted returns guaranteed by US Treasury Commodity ETF (Small Position)\tEnergy/food inflation hedge\t$25 fractional\tVaries with commodity prices\tGSG, DJP, PDBC\tAllocate 5-10% of investable funds\tHedge against import price increases 📋 CLICK-BY-CLICK SOP: Setting Up Your Dollar Protection Stack STEP 1: Open a High-Yield Savings Account (15-20 minutes) Step\tAction\tExpected Screen/Outcome 1.1\tGo to Varo.com or OpenBank.com (no minimum)\tHomepage with \"Open Account\" button 1.2\tClick \"Open Account\" or \"Get Started\"\tRegistration form appears 1.3\tEnter: Full legal name, email, phone, SSN, DOB, address\tForm fields populate 1.4\tCreate password (12+ characters, special character)\tPassword strength indicator turns green 1.5\tVerify identity (upload driver's license or passport)\tCamera/upload prompt 1.6\tLink existing checking account (routing + account #)\tBank verification screen (instant or micro-deposits) 1.7\tSet up Auto-Transfer: $25-$50/paycheck\tTransfer schedule confirmation OUTPUT\tHYSA earning 4-5% APY, FDIC insured\tConfirmation email + dashboard access STEP 2: Buy I-Bonds on TreasuryDirect (25-30 minutes first time) Step\tAction\tExpected Screen/Outcome 2.1\tGo to TreasuryDirect.gov\tBlue government site homepage 2.2\tClick \"Open an Account\" (top right)\tAccount type selection 2.3\tSelect \"Individual\"\tPersonal info form 2.4\tEnter: SSN, name, address, email, bank routing/account numbers\tMulti-page form 2.5\tCreate account password + security questions\tSecurity setup screen 2.6\tWait for Account Number email (usually within 1-3 business days)\tEmail with your account # 2.7\tLogin → Click \"BuyDirect\" tab\tBond selection screen 2.8\tSelect \"Series I\" → Enter amount ($25 minimum, $10,000 max/year)\tPurchase confirmation 2.9\tConfirm bank details → Submit\tPurchase receipt OUTPUT\tI-Bond purchased @ 4.03% composite rate\tBond appears in \"Current Holdings\" within 1 business day ⚠️ IMPORTANT: I-Bonds must be held 12 months minimum. Early redemption (12-60 months) forfeits last 3 months of interest. STEP 3: Start Fractional Gold/Silver Position (10 minutes) Step\tAction\tExpected Screen/Outcome 3.1\tOpen brokerage if you don't have one: Fidelity.com, Schwab.com, or Robinhood\tAccount opening flow 3.2\tFund account via bank transfer ($25-$100)\tTransfer confirmation 3.3\tSearch ticker: GLD (gold ETF) or SLV (silver ETF)\tStock/ETF detail page 3.4\tClick \"Buy\" → Select \"Dollars\" (fractional)\tOrder entry screen 3.5\tEnter $25-$50 → Review → Confirm\tOrder confirmation OUTPUT\tFractional gold/silver position as dollar hedge\tPosition shows in portfolio 💰 BUDGET ALLOCATION MODEL FOR LOW-INCOME EARNERS Scenario: $500 total to protect Allocation\tAmount\tWhy This Split HYSA Emergency Fund\t$250 (50%)\tLiquidity + 4-5% APY; covers unexpected expenses I-Bonds\t$150 (30%)\tLocked-in inflation protection; best risk-free return Fractional Gold ETF\t$50 (10%)\tDollar decline hedge International ETF (VXUS)\t$50 (10%)\tNon-dollar currency exposure Expected Annual Output on $500: HYSA @ 4.5%: ~$11.25 I-Bonds @ 4.03%: ~$6.05 Gold/International: Variable (historically +5-10% during dollar weakness) Total Expected Return: $20-$50+ (4-10%) while protecting purchasing power 🚫 WHAT TO AVOID Don't Do This\tWhy\tBetter Alternative Keep cash in regular checking (0.01% APY)\tLoses 3%+ to inflation annually\tMove excess to HYSA Panic-buy crypto\tHighly volatile, not a proven inflation hedge\tI-Bonds or fractional gold Take on new variable-rate debt\tRates may spike if dollar weakness continues\tFixed-rate only or pay cash Ignore the problem\tDollar has lost 11% in 12 months\tEven small steps help 📈 VISUAL: Dollar Protection Decision Flowchart Copy ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │           DO YOU HAVE MONEY TO PROTECT FROM DOLLAR DECLINE?     │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ ▼ ┌─────────────────┐ │  HOW MUCH CAN   │ │   YOU SET ASIDE │ │   MONTHLY?      │ └─────────────────┘ │ ┌───────────────────┼───────────────────┐ ▼                   ▼                   ▼ ┌──────────┐        ┌──────